commit.message: Version 1.4.2
Check for malloc failure in yajl_lex_alloc

Check need < buf->used

We're guaranteed a power of 2 so that this becomes 0, but we might as
well use a check for overflow that works in more cases.

Unsigned integer overflow is defined behaviour, so this should be safe.
record error in BUF_CHK
Add assertions
Return on error from yajl_bs_push_inline
Check for allocation errors in yajl_bs_push
Rewrite yajl_bs_push as inline function
Check buffer state inside lexer and parser
Check for error on rb_yajl_projector_build_string
Check for failed buf allocations yajl_parser
More asserts and add sanitize to extconf

Implement noop_allocs for buf_alloc_error

So that we don't free the statically allocated error buffer
Fix compiler warnings
Replace assert(0) with rb_bug
Catch exit and raise alloc error in Ruby ext
Return an error through yajl_gen_get_buf
Add assertions
Return an error from initial alloc failing
Track an error state on yajl_buf

commit.message:
Fix implicit conversion from enumeration type warning

`yajl_gen_error` is a `yajl_gen_state` not a `yajl_gen_status`.
This change adds a new value to the enum for an error when the
decremented depth is too low.

Warnings:

```
../../../../ext/yajl/yajl_gen.c:295:5: warning: implicit conversion from enumeration type 'yajl_gen_state' to different enumeration type 'yajl_gen_status'
      [-Wenum-conversion]
    DECREMENT_DEPTH;
    ^~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
../../../../ext/yajl/yajl_gen.c:181:48: note: expanded from macro 'DECREMENT_DEPTH'
    if (--(g->depth) >= YAJL_MAX_DEPTH) return yajl_gen_error;
                                        ~~~~~~ ^~~~~~~~~~~~~~
../../../../ext/yajl/yajl_gen.c:321:5: warning: implicit conversion from enumeration type 'yajl_gen_state' to different enumeration type 'yajl_gen_status'
      [-Wenum-conversion]
    DECREMENT_DEPTH;
    ^~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
../../../../ext/yajl/yajl_gen.c:181:48: note: expanded from macro 'DECREMENT_DEPTH'
    if (--(g->depth) >= YAJL_MAX_DEPTH) return yajl_gen_error;
                                        ~~~~~~ ^~~~~~~~~~~~~~
```

Co-authored-by: John Hawthorn <john@hawthorn.email>
